      scene: `The hallway was mostly quiet. It was getting close to curfew, and most of the students had gone back to their dormitories. The faint orange glow of the wall torches changed the look of the halls drastically. As you walk down the halls, you hear the faint, dull rhythm of music. A low thud, slow, steady, with the faint twang of a string instrument. You follow the noise, hearing an angelic voice singing along to the tribal beat.\n\nYou stop a moment to listen, losing yourself if just for a moment in the beat. Seth notices you, looks up, smiles then returns to his music. For a moment, it's just the two of you and the music. The song begins to trail off, and he stops playing, setting his instrument aside.\n\n"Did you enjoy that?" He asks, you can't tell if he actually wants your validation, or if he's just striking up conversation. You tell him you did, and he smiles again.\n\n"It's a song that has been in my family for generations. My mother used to sing it to me when I was young. It reminds me of her." You can see in his eyes for a moment that he is not here, not in this moment with you. He is far away, in a time that seems out of reach. Then he's back.\n\n"Well regardless, I really hope you liked it." He said, going back to his music. You walk away, listening to the music as you go.`,
