      scene: `The library is mostly quiet. The occasional turning of page can be heard over the faint ambient whispering that fills the room.\n\nYou spot Anuhea sitting alone with a book detailing the supposed evidence for the existence of Nargles. As you approach her, she ignores you. She seems simultaneously engrossed and disinterested in the book she's reading.\n\nYou try to get her attention, but she seems to be 'choosing' to ignore you.\n\nA little persistence gets you a reaction as she looks up from her book. She says nothing, only raises an eyebrow at you as you stand before her.\n\nYour greeting is met with an unblinking stare, and a long, awkward silence. Finally, she speaks to you. "Did you need this book or something…?"\n\nYou glance around, seeing a stack of books about magical creatures and their various habits, all pulled down recently by her, and all but the one in her hand laying with their back cover up, indicating she had already finished them.\n\nYou tell her you're just trying to make new friends, and that she looks like someone interesting, but before you can finish exhaling after you speak, she responds.\n\n"Try somewhere else." Her words are short, cold and finite. She effectively ends the conversation, and any smooth transition to another one with a single sentence, leaving you with only one option. You leave for now, but you notice a small tug at the side of her lips as if she were trying not to smile. You question whether or not your statement about her looking like an interesting person had made an impression or not.`,
